-- Home Depot marketing chief leaving
-- 
-- Wed Oct 17, 2007 5:54pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/17/us-homedepot-marketing-idUSN1735334920071017

 

 ATLANTA  (Reuters) - Retailer Home Depot Inc ( HD.N ) said on Wednesday that its chief marketing officer was leaving to pursue other opportunities. 

 Chairman and Chief Executive Frank Blake announced the departure of Roger Adams in a memo to staffers, which was made available to Reuters by the company. Adams joined the home improvement retailer in February 2005 as senior vice president of marketing and was named chief marketing officer in October 2006, the memo said. John Ross, vice president of advertising, has been named interim chief of Home Depot's marketing organization, the company said. (Reporting by  Karen Jacobs )